conbody.p:
The localisation comments must be enclosed within the comment brackets
/*&...*/. These comment brackets include a set of tags to provide more
details about the RLS item.

li.p:
 @description:
This is mandatory tag used to provide a description about the RLS item. This
tag is used to provide the following information to the translator:

 @restriction:
This is an optional tag used to specify the scope of the RLS item. The possible
values for this tag are:

li.codeblock:
/*& @description Must point to the happy bugle wave file, used as a ring tone and displayed to the user in the ring-tone selection dialog.
@localize yes
@restriction file
*/
rls_string STRING_2 "happy bugle.wav"

li.p:
 @uispec:
This is an optional tag used to specify where in the specifications document
the RLS item appears.
